Food	#298.	 joint, piece de resistance [Fr.], roast and boiled
Heat	#382.	 hot enough to roast an ox, hot enough to boil an egg. fiery
Calefaction	#384.	 liquefy &c.. burn, inflame, roast, toast, fry, grill, singe, parch, bake, torrefy, scorch
Ridicule	#856.	 tease [ridicule lightly], badinage, banter, rally, chaff, joke, twit, quiz, roast
Celebration	#883.	 kill the fatted calf, hold jubilee, roast an ox. Adj. celebrating &c. v.
Disrespect	#929.	 roast, turn into ridicule
Condemnation	#971.	Punishment dress, dress down, give a dressing, trim, warm, wipe, tund, cob, bang, strap, comb, lash, lick, larrup, wallop, whop, flog, scourge, whip, birch, cane, give the stick, switch, flagellate, horsewhip, bastinado, towel, rub down with an oaken towel, rib roast, dust one's jacket, fustigate, pitch into, lay about one, beat black and blue
